From 17646d4b15e4cd804b8f1170ad5ed164362fd07b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Takumi Ando <takumi@spacecubics.com>
Date: Thu, 5 Mar 2026 16:07:11 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] rtc: zynqmp: Always program Max_Tick and preserve
 fractional calibration

The current driver programs the CALIB_WRITE register only when
CALIB_READ register reads as zero:

    ret = readl(... + RTC_CALIB_RD);
    if (!ret)
        writel(calibval, ... + RTC_CALIB_WR);

However, according to the Versal Adaptive SoC Register Reference (AM012),
the value returned by CALIB_RD after reset is undefined.
As a result, the driver may skip programming the calibration register and
leave the RTC running with an incorrect Max_Tick value.

The Max_Tick field determines the number of oscillator cycles per second
and must be set according to the RTC clock frequency (e.g. 0x7FFF for a
32.768 kHz oscillator).
Leaving this value unprogrammed can cause the RTC to tick at the wrong rate.

Update the driver to always program Max_Tick from the Device Tree
"calibration" property (or the default value) while preserving the
fractional calibration bits currently stored in hardware.
The fractional correction may be adjusted dynamically (e.g. for temperature
compensation) and should not be overwritten during probe.

This ensures the RTC always uses the correct Max_Tick value without
destroying any existing fractional calibration.

Signed-off-by: Takumi Ando <takumi@spacecubics.com>
---
 drivers/rtc/rtc-zynqmp.c | 11 ++++++-----
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/rtc/rtc-zynqmp.c b/drivers/rtc/rtc-zynqmp.c
index a4101f0a10b1..30a8dbba5a33 100644
--- a/drivers/rtc/rtc-zynqmp.c
+++ b/drivers/rtc/rtc-zynqmp.c
@@ -279,6 +279,8 @@ static int xlnx_rtc_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 {
 	struct xlnx_rtc_dev *xrtcdev;
 	u32 calibval;
+	u32 fraction;
+	u32 max_tick;
 	int ret;
 
 	xrtcdev = devm_kzalloc(&pdev->dev, sizeof(*xrtcdev), GFP_KERNEL);
@@ -331,15 +333,14 @@ static int xlnx_rtc_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		xrtcdev->freq = RTC_FREQ_DEF;
 	}
 
+	/* Always program Max_Tick from DT, preserve fractional calibration bits. */
 	ret = of_property_read_u32(pdev->dev.of_node, "calibration", &calibval);
 	if (ret) {
 		calibval = RTC_CALIB_DEF;
 	}
-
-	ret = readl(xrtcdev->reg_base + RTC_CALIB_RD);
-	if (!ret) {
-		writel(calibval, (xrtcdev->reg_base + RTC_CALIB_WR));
-	}
+	max_tick = calibval & RTC_TICK_MASK;
+	fraction = readl(xrtcdev->reg_base + RTC_CALIB_RD) & (RTC_FR_EN | RTC_FR_MASK);
+	writel(fraction | max_tick, (xrtcdev->reg_base + RTC_CALIB_WR));
 
 	xlnx_init_rtc(xrtcdev);
 
